# Static Site Rules

## Stack

Vanilla HTML, CSS, JavaScript only. No React. No Node. No bundlers. No frameworks.
All data is fetched from Supabase public endpoints via the anon key injected by Cloudflare Worker at /assets/supabase-env.js
No backend logic in the site/ folder. site/ is a static site only.
Data Access

Always read from Supabase via the injected client. Never read from local CSV files in production paths.
Supabase credentials arrive via /assets/supabase-env.js — do not hardcode them.
Always handle Supabase fetch errors gracefully with a visible error state.
Style

**Marketing shell (`site/` except `/terminal/`):** UI Prompt v2 — light editorial / canvas (`docs/FX_REGIME_LAB_UI_PROMPT_V2.md`): Playfair + DM Sans + JetBrains Mono; light backgrounds. Pair accents stay EUR/USD #4da6ff, USD/JPY #ff9944, USD/INR #e74c3c where applicable.

**Research terminal (`site/terminal/`):** dark desk theme (background ~#0a0e1a, data-dense). Same pair accent hex values.

Do not introduce new fonts, color schemes, or UI frameworks without explicit instruction.
Anti-Patterns — NEVER Suggest These

React, Vue, Angular, or any JS framework
Node.js imports or require()
localStorage for sensitive data
Hardcoded Supabase keys anywhere in site/ files
New CDN dependencies without explicit approval
